As an AI language model, I am not sure what you mean by an "output type". However, I assume you want to convert a Word document to PDF format using Aspose.Words for Java and retrieve the PDF document as a byte array instead of saving it to a file.

You can use the `ByteArrayOutputStream` class in conjunction with Aspose.Words and Aspose.PDF for Java to achieve this. Here is some sample code that demonstrates how to do this:

```java
import com.aspose.words.Document;
import com.aspose.words.SaveFormat;
import com.aspose.pdf.devices.PdfSaveOptions;
import com.aspose.pdf.facades.PdfConverter;

import java.io.ByteArrayInputStream;
import java.io.ByteArrayOutputStream;
import java.io.IOException;

public class WordToPdfConverter {

    public static byte[] convertToPdf(byte[] wordDoc) throws IOException {
        // load Word document from a byte array
        ByteArrayInputStream input = new ByteArrayInputStream(wordDoc);
        Document doc = new Document(input);

        // set PDF save options
        PdfSaveOptions saveOptions = new PdfSaveOptions();
        saveOptions.setSaveFormat(SaveFormat.PDF);

        // convert Word document to PDF
        ByteArrayOutputStream output = new ByteArrayOutputStream();
        doc.save(output, saveOptions);

        // load PDF document from the output byte array
        byte[] pdfDoc = output.toByteArray();
        PdfConverter converter = new PdfConverter();
        converter.bindPdf(new ByteArrayInputStream(pdfDoc));

        // extract PDF pages as images and append them to a new PDF document
        ByteArrayOutputStream finalOutput = new ByteArrayOutputStream();
        converter.doConvert();
        converter.saveAsTIFF(finalOutput);

        // return the final PDF document as a byte array
        return finalOutput.toByteArray();
    }

}
```

Note that this code loads a Word document from a byte array, converts it to a PDF document, and then extracts the PDF pages as images before appending them to a new PDF document. Finally, the code returns the byte array of the final PDF document. You can modify this code to suit your specific requirements.

Aspose.Cells is a library primarily intended for working with Microsoft Excel documents, not Word documents. As for Word to PDF conversions, Aspose.Words is the appropriate library to use.

That being said, if you have a Word document that contains Excel tables or charts and you want to convert it to PDF format using Aspose.Cells, you can use the following sample code as a starting point:

```java
import com.aspose.cells.Workbook;
import com.aspose.cells.WorkbookRender;
import com.aspose.words.Document;
import com.aspose.words.SaveFormat;

import java.io.ByteArrayInputStream;
import java.io.ByteArrayOutputStream;
import java.io.IOException;

public class WordToPdfConverter {

    public static byte[] convertToPdf(byte[] wordDoc) throws IOException {
        // load Word document from a byte array
        ByteArrayInputStream input = new ByteArrayInputStream(wordDoc);
        Document doc = new Document(input);

        // save Word document to a temporary file
        ByteArrayOutputStream tempFile = new ByteArrayOutputStream();
        doc.save(tempFile, SaveFormat.DOCX);

        // load temporary file into an Aspose.Cells Workbook
        ByteArrayInputStream tempInput = new ByteArrayInputStream(tempFile.toByteArray());
        Workbook workbook = new Workbook(tempInput);

        // create an instance of the WorkbookRender class
        WorkbookRender wr = new WorkbookRender(workbook, new PdfSaveOptions());

        // set rending options
        wr.setHideAutoFilterDropDowns(true);
        wr.getSaveOptions().setOnePagePerSheet(true);

        // render workbook to PDF
        ByteArrayOutputStream output = new ByteArrayOutputStream();
        wr.toPdf(output);

        // return the PDF document as a byte array
        return output.toByteArray();
    }

}
```

In this code, we first load the Word document from a byte array and save it to a temporary file in DOCX format (which can be opened by Aspose.Cells). Next, we load the temporary file into an Aspose.Cells Workbook and use the WorkbookRender class to convert it to PDF format. Finally, we return the resulting PDF document as a byte array.

Note that this code assumes that the Word document contains an Excel table or chart that is supported by Aspose.Cells.

